JB11305 Class5 WelcomeToTheWorldofVersionControlSystem 
======================================================

Click on https://github.com/ then click on signup, please provide username, password and email and click on account creation

1) I want to add a file into repository
2) I want to add folder and inside folder I want to add file2


What is repository
==================
>> It is place where we can share our data.

>> It's a kind of central server.[Initial definition]

>> commit means saving the contain

What is GIT
===========

>> GIT is a repository where we can store file and folder for tracking the changes.

Green >>> Adding the changes

Red >> removing the changes

WOW with GIT
============

IN git we have 4 area's

1) working directory> It's a place from where you are running the command

2) Stagging area> Compressing and encryption

3) Local repository> We will create one folder, and run git init command into it.

4) Remote repository> Here with the help of URL we are doing the changes.


git clone <URL>
================

This command used to copy remote repository to local repository

Example: git clone https://github.com/JanbaskDevops/Batch2.git


ubuntu $ git clone https://github.com/JanbaskDevops/Batch2.git
Cloning into 'Batch2'...
remote: Enumerating objects: 24, done.
remote: Counting objects: 100% (24/24), done.
remote: Compressing objects: 100% (24/24), done.
remote: Total 24 (delta 12), reused 0 (delta 0), pack-reused 0
Unpacking objects: 100% (24/24), 9.10 KiB | 2.28 MiB/s, done.
ubuntu $ ls
Batch2  filesystem  snap

ubuntu $ cd Batch2/

ubuntu $ ls
'Class1- Introduction to DevOPs'                      'Class3- Repository'
'Class2- DevOps tools installation and introduction'


How to create local repository
==============================
ubuntu $ mkdir Batch4
ubuntu $ cd Batch4
ubuntu $ git init
Initialized empty Git repository in /root/Batch4/.git/

What is git init command
========================
git init will convert folder into repository


How to add username and password into repository
================================================

ubuntu $ git config --list  
core.repositoryformatversion=0
core.filemode=true
core.bare=false
core.logallrefupdates=true


git config --global user.name "Umesh"
git config --global user.email "Umesh@gmail.com"

ubuntu $ git config --global user.name "Umesh"
ubuntu $ git config --global user.email "Umes@gmail.com"
ubuntu $ git config --list

user.name=Umesh
user.email=Umes@gmail.com
core.repositoryformatversion=0
core.filemode=true
core.bare=false
core.logallrefupdates=true
Casestudy: Suppose, you are working on organisation, and they ask you to upload your image into portal.
            maximum image size: 2 MB
            Image you have: 100 MB

what you do? >> compressing on image
100MB >> 80MB >> 65MB >> 55MB............ 1MB

In this scenario, multiple compression is happening, and encryption also happening


